{"title_page": "Italy at the 1988 Summer Olympics", "text_new": "{{infobox country at games\n| NOC = ITA\n| NOCname = [[Italian National Olympic Committee]]\n| games = Summer Olympics\n| year = 1988\n| flagcaption = \n| oldcode = \n| website = {{url|www.coni.it }}&nbsp;{{in lang|it}}\n| location = [[Seoul]]\n| competitors = 253 (212 men, 41 women)\n| sports = 23\n| flagbearer = [[Pietro Mennea]]\n| rank = 10\n| gold = 6\n| silver = 4\n| bronze = 4\n| officials = \n| appearances = auto\n| app_begin_year = \n| app_end_year = \n| summerappearances = \n| winterappearances = \n| seealso = [[Italy at the 1906 Intercalated Games|1906]] Intercalated Games\n}}\n\n'''[[Italy]]''' competed at the '''[[1988 Summer Olympics]]''' in [[Seoul]], [[South Korea]]. 253 competitors, 212 men and 41 women, took part in 140 events in 23 sports.<ref name=\"sports-reference\">{{cite web|url=https://www.sports-reference.com/olympics/countries/ITA/summer/1988/ |title=Italy at the 1988 Summer Games |accessdate=2011-07-22 |work=sports-reference.com |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110630123952/http://www.sports-reference.com/olympics/countries/ITA/summer/1988/ |archivedate=2011-06-30 }}</ref>\n\n==Medalists==\n\n===Gold===\n* [[Gelindo Bordin]] \u2014 Athletics, Men's Marathon\n* [[Giovanni Parisi]] \u2014 Boxing, Men's Featherweight\n* [[Stefano Cerioni]] \u2014 Fencing, Men's Foil Individual Competition\n* [[Vincenzo Maenza]] \u2014 Wrestling, Men's Greco-Roman Light Flyweight \n* [[Carmine Abbagnale]], [[Giuseppe Abbagnale]] and [[Giuseppe Di Capua]] \u2014 Rowing, Men's Coxed Pairs  \n* [[Agostino Abbagnale]], [[Davide Tizzano]], [[Piero Poli]] and [[Gianluca Farina]] \u2014 Rowing, Men's Quadruple Sculls\n\n===Silver===\n* [[Carlo Massullo]] \u2014 Modern Pentathlon, Individual Competition\n* [[Carlo Massullo]], [[Daniele Masala]] and [[Gianluca Tiberti]] \u2014 Modern Pentathlon, Team Competition\n* [[Salvatore Antibo]] \u2014 Athletics, Men's 10.000 metres\n* [[Francesca Bortolozzi-Borella]], [[Dorina Vaccaroni]], [[Margherita Zalaffi]], [[Annapia Gandolfi]] and [[Lucia Traversa]] \u2014 Fencing, Women's  Foil Team Competition\n\n=== Bronze===\n* [[Maurizio Damilano]] \u2014 Athletics, Men's 20&nbsp;km Walk\n* [[Giovanni Scalzo]] \u2014 Fencing, Men's Sabre Individual Competition\n* [[Stefano Battistelli]] \u2014 Swimming, Men's 400 metres Individual Medley \n* [[Gianfranco Dalla Barba]], [[Marco Marin]], [[Ferdinando Meglio]], [[Giovanni Scalzo]] and [[Massimo Cavaliere]] \u2014 Fencing, Men's Sabre Team Competition\n\n==Archery==\n{{main|Archery at the 1988 Summer Olympics}}\n[[Giancarlo Ferrari]], competing in his fifth Olympic archery contest, dropped to 33rd place in the field.  Fellow veteran [[Ilario Di Bu\u00f2]] advanced to the quarterfinal, nearly missing a semifinal berth.  The Italians also just missed the cutoff for the final by one ranking in the team round.\n\n'''Men's Individual Competition:'''\n* [[Ilario Di Bu\u00f2]] &ndash; Quarterfinal (\u2192 13th place)\n* [[Andrea Parenti]] &ndash; Preliminary Round (\u2192 28th place)\n* [[Giancarlo Ferrari]] &ndash; Preliminary Round (\u2192 33rd place)\n\n'''Men's Team Competition:'''\n* Di Buo, Parenti, and Ferrari &ndash; Semifinal (\u2192 9th place)\n\n==Athletics==\n{{main|Athletics at the 1988 Summer Olympics}}\n'''Men's 10,000 metres''' \n* [[Salvatore Antibo]] \n:* First Round &mdash; 28:09.35\n:* Final &mdash; 27:23.55 (\u2192 [[File:Silver medal with cup.svg|16px|Silver]] '''Silver Medal''')\n\n* [[Alberto Cova]] \n:* First Round &mdash; 28:43.84 (\u2192 did not advance)\n\n'''Men's Marathon''' \n* [[Gelindo Bordin]] \n:* Final &mdash; 2\"10:32 (\u2192 [[Image:Gold medal with cup.svg|16px|Gold]] '''Gold Medal''')\n\n* [[Orlando Pizzolato]] \n:* Final &mdash; 2\"15:20 (\u2192 16th place)\n\n* [[Gianni Poli]] \n:* Final &mdash; 2\"16:07 (\u2192 19th place)\n\n'''Men's 3,000 m Steeplechase'''\n* [[Alessandro Lambruschini]]\n:# Heat &mdash; 8:32.59 \n:# Semi Final &mdash; 8:16.92\n:# Final &mdash; 8:12.17 (\u2192 4th place)\n\n* [[Francesco Panetta]]\n:* Heat &mdash; 8:29.75 \n:* Semi Final &mdash; 8:17.23\n:* Final &mdash; 8:17.79 (\u2192 9th place)\n\n'''Men's Hammer Throw'''\n* [[Lucio Serrani]]\n:* Qualifying Heat &mdash; 70.50m (\u2192 did not advance)\n\n'''Men's Shot Put'''\n* [[Alessandro Andrei]]\n:* Qualifying Heat &ndash; 20.18m\n:* Final &ndash; 20.36m (\u2192 7th place)\n\n'''Men's Long Jump''' \n* [[Giovanni Evangelisti]] \n:* Qualification &mdash; 7.81m\n:* Final &mdash; 8.08m (\u2192 4th place)\n\n'''Men's 20&nbsp;km Walk'''\n* [[Maurizio Damilano]]\n:* Final &mdash; 1:20:14 (\u2192 [[Image:Bronze medal.svg|16x16px]] '''Bronze  Medal''')\n\n* [[Giovanni De Benedictis]]\n:* Final &mdash; 1:20:14 (\u2192 6th place)\n\n* [[Carlo Mattioli]]\n:* Final &mdash; 1:22:58 (\u2192 19th place)\n\n'''Men's 50&nbsp;km Walk'''\n* [[Raffaello Ducceschi]]\n:* Final &mdash; 3'45:43 (\u2192 8th place)\n\n* [[Giovanni Perricelli]]\n:* Final &mdash; 3'47:14 (\u2192 11th place)\n\n* [[Sandro Bellucci]]\n:* Final &mdash; 4'04:56 (\u2192 32nd place) \n<br>\n'''Women's Marathon''' \n* [[Laura Fogli]] \n:* Final &mdash; 2\"27.49 (\u2192 6th place)\n\n* [[Maria Curatolo]] \n:* Final &mdash; 2\"30.14 (\u2192 8th place)\n \n* [[Antonella Bizioli]] \n:* Final &mdash; 2\"34.38 (\u2192 23rd place)\n\n==Boxing==\n{{main|Boxing at the 1988 Summer Olympics}}\n'''Men's Flyweight (&ndash; 51&nbsp;kg)''' \n* [[Andrea Mannai]]\n:* First Round &mdash; Lost to [[Arthur Johnson (boxer)|Arthur Johnson]] (USA), 0:5\n\n'''Men's Featherweight'''\n* [[Giovanni Parisi]]\n\n'''Men's Lightweight'''\n* [[Giorgio Campanella]]\n\n'''Men's Light-Middleweight'''\n* [[Vincenzo Nardiello]]\n\n'''Men's Middleweight'''\n* [[Michele Mastrodonato]]\n\n'''Men's Light-Heavyweight'''\n* [[Andrea Magi]]\n\n'''Men's Heavyweight'''\n* [[Luigi Gaudiano]]\n\n==Canoeing==\n{{main|Canoeing at the 1988 Summer Olympics}}\n\n==Cycling==\n{{main|Cycling at the 1988 Summer Olympics}}\nEighteen cyclists, fourteen men and four women, represented Italy in 1988.\n\n;[[Cycling at the 1988 Summer Olympics \u2013 Men's individual road race|Men's road race]]\n* [[Roberto Pelliconi]]\n* [[Fabrizio Bontempi]]\n* [[Gianluca Bortolami]]\n\n;[[Cycling at the 1988 Summer Olympics \u2013 Men's team time trial|Men's team time trial]]\n* [[Roberto Maggioni]]\n* [[Eros Poli]]\n* [[Mario Scirea]]\n* [[Flavio Vanzella]]\n\n;[[Cycling at the 1988 Summer Olympics \u2013 Men's sprint|Men's sprint]]\n* [[Andrea Faccini]]\n\n;[[Cycling at the 1988 Summer Olympics \u2013 Men's individual pursuit|Men's individual pursuit]]\n* [[Ivan Beltrami]]\n\n;[[Cycling at the 1988 Summer Olympics \u2013 Men's team pursuit|Men's team pursuit]]\n* [[Ivan Beltrami]]\n* [[Gianpaolo Grisandi]]\n* [[David Solari (cyclist)|David Solari]]\n* [[Fabrizio Trezzi]]\n* [[Fabio Baldato]]\n\n;[[Cycling at the 1988 Summer Olympics \u2013 Men's points race|Men's points race]]\n* [[Giovanni Lombardi]]\n\n;[[Cycling at the 1988 Summer Olympics \u2013 Women's individual road race|Women's road race]]\n* [[Imelda Chiappa]] &mdash; 2:00:52 (\u2192 15th place)\n* [[Maria Canins]] &mdash; 2:00:52 (\u2192 32nd place)\n* [[Roberta Bonanomi]] &mdash; 2:00:52 (\u2192 45th place)\n\n;[[Cycling at the 1988 Summer Olympics \u2013 Women's sprint|Women's sprint]]\n* [[Elisabetta Fanton]]\n\n==Diving==\n{{main|Diving at the 1988 Summer Olympics}}\n\n==Equestrian==\n{{main|Equestrian at the 1988 Summer Olympics}}\n\n==Fencing==\n{{main|Fencing at the 1988 Summer Olympics}}\n20 fencers, 15 men and 5 women, represented Italy in 1988.\n\n;[[Fencing at the 1988 Summer Olympics \u2013 Men's foil|Men's foil]]\n* [[Stefano Cerioni]]\n* [[Mauro Numa]]\n* [[Andrea Borella]]\n\n;[[Fencing at the 1988 Summer Olympics \u2013 Men's team foil|Men's team foil]]\n* [[Andrea Borella]], [[Stefano Cerioni]], [[Federico Cervi]], [[Andrea Cipressa]], [[Mauro Numa]]\n\n;[[Fencing at the 1988 Summer Olympics \u2013 Men's \u00e9p\u00e9e|Men's \u00e9p\u00e9e]]\n* [[Sandro Cuomo]]\n* [[Stefano Pantano]]\n* [[Angelo Mazzoni]]\n\n;[[Fencing at the 1988 Summer Olympics \u2013 Men's team \u00e9p\u00e9e|Men's team \u00e9p\u00e9e]]\n* [[Stefano Bellone]], [[Andrea Bermond Des Ambrois]], [[Sandro Cuomo]], [[Angelo Mazzoni]], [[Stefano Pantano]]\n\n;[[Fencing at the 1988 Summer Olympics \u2013 Men's sabre|Men's sabre]]\n* [[Giovanni Scalzo]]\n* [[Gianfranco Dalla Barba]]\n* [[Marco Marin]]\n\n;[[Fencing at the 1988 Summer Olympics \u2013 Men's team sabre|Men's team sabre]]\n* [[Giovanni Scalzo]], [[Marco Marin]], [[Gianfranco Dalla Barba]], [[Ferdinando Meglio]], [[Massimo Cavaliere]]\n\n;[[Fencing at the 1988 Summer Olympics \u2013 Women's foil|Women's foil]]\n* [[Margherita Zalaffi]]\n* [[Dorina Vaccaroni]]\n* [[Annapia Gandolfi]]\n\n;[[Fencing at the 1988 Summer Olympics \u2013 Women's team foil|Women's team foil]]\n* [[Dorina Vaccaroni]], [[Margherita Zalaffi]], [[Francesca Bortolozzi-Borella]], [[Lucia Traversa]], [[Annapia Gandolfi]]\n\n==Football==\n{{main|Football at the 1988 Summer Olympics}}\n'''Men's Team Competition'''\n*'''Preliminary Round (Group B)''' \n:* Defeated [[Guatemala national football team|Guatemala]] (5-2)\n:* Lost to [[Zambia national football team|Zambia]] (0-4)\n:* Defeated [[Iraq national football team|Iraq]] (2-0)\n*'''Quarterfinals''' \n:* Defeated [[Sweden national football team|Sweden]] (2-1)\n*'''Semifinals'''\n:* Lost to [[Soviet Union national football team|Soviet Union]] (2-3)\n*'''Bronze Medal Match''' \n:* Lost to [[West Germany national football team|West Germany]] (0-3)\n\n*'''Team Roster'''\n{{Col-begin-small}}\n{{Col-2}}\n# [[Stefano Tacconi]] (gk)  \n# [[Roberto Cravero]] \n# [[Andrea Carnevale]] \n# [[Luigi De Agostini]] \n# [[Ciro Ferrara]] \n# [[Mauro Tassotti]] \n# [[Angelo Colombo]] \n# [[Luca Pellegrini (footballer, born 1963)|Luca Pellegrini]] \n# [[Massimo Brambati]] \n# [[Stefano Carobbi]]   \n# [[Massimo Crippa]] \n# [[Giuliano Giuliani]]\n# [[Paolo Virdis]]\n# [[Ruggiero Rizzitelli]]\n# [[Roberto Galia]]  \n# [[Giuseppe Iachini]] \n# [[Stefano Desideri]]  \n# [[Massimo Mauro]] \n# [[Alberigo Evani]] \n# [[Gianluca Pagliuca]] (gk)  \n'''Head Coach''': [[Francesco Rocca]]\n{{Col-end}}\n\n==Gymnastics==\n{{main|Gymnastics at the 1988 Summer Olympics}}\n\n==Judo==\n{{main|Judo at the 1988 Summer Olympics}}\n\n==Modern pentathlon==\n{{main|Modern pentathlon at the 1988 Summer Olympics}}\nThree male pentathletes represented Italy in 1988. Carlo Massullo won an individual silver and the team won silver too.\n\n'''Men's Individual Competition:'''\n* [[Carlo Massullo]] &ndash; 5379 pts (\u2192 [[Image:Med 2.png|Silver]] '''Silver Medal''')\n* [[Daniele Masala]] &ndash; 5152 pts (\u2192 10th place)\n* [[Gianluca Tiberti]] &ndash; 5040 pts (\u2192 17th place)\n\n'''Men's Team Competition:'''\n* Massullo, Masala, and Tiberti &ndash; 15571pts (\u2192 [[Image:Med 2.png|Silver]] '''Silver Medal''')\n\n==Rhythmic gymnastics==\n{{main|Rhythmic gymnastics at the 1988 Summer Olympics}}\n\n==Rowing==\n{{main|Rowing at the 1988 Summer Olympics}}\n\n==Sailing==\n{{main|Sailing at the 1988 Summer Olympics}}\n\n==Shooting==\n{{main|Shooting at the 1988 Summer Olympics}}\n\n==Swimming==\n{{main|Swimming at the 1988 Summer Olympics}}\n'''Men's 100 m Freestyle'''\n* [[Roberto Gleria]]\n:* Heat &ndash; 50.97 (\u2192 did not advance, 18th place)\n\n'''Men's 200 m Freestyle'''\n* [[Roberto Gleria]]\n:* Heat &ndash; 1:49.51\n:* B-Final &ndash; 1:49.28 (\u2192 9th place)\n\n* [[Giorgio Lamberti]]\n:* Heat &ndash; 1:50.47\n:* B-Final &ndash; scratched (\u2192 did not advance, no ranking)\n\n'''Men's 400 m Freestyle'''\n* [[Giorgio Lamberti]]\n:* Heat &ndash; 3:53.29\n:* B-Final &ndash; scratched (\u2192 did not advance, no ranking)\n\n* [[Roberto Gleria]]\n:* Heat &ndash; 3:56.33 (\u2192 did not advance, 19th place)\n\n'''Men's 1500 m Freestyle'''\n* [[Luca Pellegrini (swimmer)|Luca Pellegrini]]\n:* Heat &ndash; 15:18.80 (\u2192 did not advance, 10th place)\n\n* [[Stefano Battistelli]]\n:* Heat &ndash; 15:36.54 (\u2192 did not advance, 20th place)\n\n'''Men's 100 m Backstroke'''\n* [[Valerio Giambalvo]]\n:* Heat &ndash; 59.48 (\u2192 did not advance, 37th place)\n\n'''Men's 200 m Backstroke'''\n* [[Stefano Battistelli]]\n:* Heat &ndash; 2:03.63\n:* B-Final &ndash; scratched (\u2192 did not advance, no ranking)\n\n'''Men's 100 m Breaststroke'''\n* [[Gianni Minervini (swimmer)|Gianni Minervini]]\n:* Heat &ndash; 1:02.86\n:* Final &ndash; 1:02.93 (\u2192 7th place)\n\n'''Men's 100 m Butterfly'''\n* [[Leonardo Michelotti]]\n:* Heat &ndash; 55.83 (\u2192 did not advance, 22nd place)\n\n* [[Valerio Giambalvo]]\n:* Heat &ndash; 56.57 (\u2192 did not advance, 28th place)\n\n'''Men's 200 m Individual Medley'''\n* [[Luca Sacchi]]\n:* Heat &ndash; 2:05.45\n:* B-Final &ndash; 2:05.68 (\u2192 13th place)\n\n* [[Roberto Cassio]]\n:* Heat &ndash; 2:05.88 (\u2192 did not advance, 18th place)\n\n'''Men's 400 m Individual Medley'''\n* [[Stefano Battistelli]]\n:* Heat &ndash; 4:20.43\n:* Final &ndash; 4:18.01 (\u2192 [[Image:Med 3.png|Bronze]] '''Bronze Medal''')\n\n* [[Luca Sacchi]]\n:* Heat &ndash; 4:23.37\n:* Final &ndash; 4:23.23 (\u2192 7th place)\n\n'''Men's 4 \u00d7 100 m Freestyle Relay'''\n* [[Fabrizio Rampazzo]], [[Giorgio Lamberti]], [[Andrea Ceccarini]], and [[Roberto Gleria]]\n:* Heat &ndash; 3:23.35\n* [[Roberto Gleria]], [[Giorgio Lamberti]], [[Fabrizio Rampazzo]], and [[Andrea Ceccarini]]\n:* Final &ndash; 3:22.93 (\u2192 8th place)\n\n'''Men's 4 \u00d7 200 m Freestyle Relay'''\n* [[Massimo Trevisan]], [[Fabrizio Rampazzo]], [[Valerio Giambalvo]], and [[Roberto Gleria]]\n:* Heat &ndash; 7:21.85\n* [[Roberto Gleria]], [[Giorgio Lamberti]], [[Massimo Trevisan]], and [[Valerio Giambalvo]]\n:* Final &ndash; 7:16.00 (\u2192 5th place)\n\n'''Men's 4 \u00d7 100 m Medley Relay'''\n* [[Valerio Giambalvo]], [[Gianni Minervini (swimmer)|Gianni Minervini]], [[Leonardo Michelotti]], and [[Roberto Gleria]]\n:* Heat &ndash; 3:52.06 (\u2192 did not advance, 15th place)\n<br>\n'''Women's 100 m Freestyle'''\n* [[Silvia Persi]]\n:* Heat &ndash; 58.22 (\u2192 did not advance, 29th place)\n\n'''Women's 200 m Freestyle'''\n* [[Silvia Persi]]\n:* Heat &ndash; 2:04.40 (\u2192 did not advance, 23rd place)\n\n'''Women's 400 m Freestyle'''\n* [[Manuela Melchiorri]]\n:* Heat &ndash; 4:15.40\n:* B-Final &ndash; 4:14.90 (\u2192 14th place)\n\n'''Women's 800 m Freestyle'''\n* [[Manuela Melchiorri]]\n:* Heat &ndash; 8:40.63 (\u2192 did not advance, 12th place)\n\n'''Women's 100 m Backstroke'''\n* [[Lorenza Vigarani]]\n:* Heat &ndash; 1:03.96\n:* B-Final &ndash; 1:03.88 (\u2192 13th place)\n\n* [[Manuela Carosi]]\n:* Heat &ndash; 1:04.69\n:* B-Final &ndash; 1:03.80 (\u2192 11th place)\n\n'''Women's 200 m Backstroke'''\n* [[Lorenza Vigarani]]\n:* Heat &ndash; 2:17.35\n:* B-Final &ndash; 2:18.69 (\u2192 13th place)\n\n'''Women's 100 m Breaststroke'''\n* [[Manuela Dalla Valle]]\n:* Heat &ndash; 1:11.25\n:* B-Final &ndash; 1:10.95 (\u2192 12th place)\n\n'''Women's 200 m Breaststroke'''\n* [[Manuela Dalla Valle]]\n:* Heat &ndash; 2:30.60\n:* Final &ndash; 2:29.86 (\u2192 8th place)\n\n* [[Annalisa Nisiro]]\n:* Heat &ndash; 2:32.77\n:* B-Final &ndash; 2:31.19 (\u2192 12th place)\n\n'''Women's 100 m Butterfly'''\n* [[Ilaria Tocchini]]\n:* Heat &ndash; 1:02.07\n:* B-Final &ndash; 1:02.78 (\u2192 16th place)\n\n* [[Emanuela Viola]]\n:* Heat &ndash; 1:03.91 (\u2192 did not advance, 24th place)\n\n'''Women's 200 m Individual Medley'''\n* [[Roberta Felotti]]\n:* Heat &ndash; 2:19.62\n:* B-Final &ndash; 2:19.63 (\u2192 13th place)\n\n* [[Manuela Dalla Valle]]\n:* Heat &ndash; 2:22.85 (\u2192 did not advance, 25th place)\n\n'''Women's 400 m Individual Medley'''\n* [[Roberta Felotti]]\n:* Heat &ndash; 4:49.20\n:* B-Final &ndash; 4:49.53 (\u2192 9th place)\n\n'''Women's 4 \u00d7 100 m Medley Relay'''\n* [[Lorenza Vigarani]], [[Manuela Dalla Valle]], [[Ilara Tocchini]], and [[Silvia Persi]]\n:* Heat &ndash; 4:14.68\n:* Final &ndash; 4:13.85 (\u2192 8th place)\n\n==Table tennis==\n{{main|Table tennis at the 1988 Summer Olympics}}\n\n==Tennis==\n{{main|Tennis at the 1988 Summer Olympics}}\n'''Men's Singles Competition'''\n* [[Paolo Can\u00e8]]\n:* First round &mdash; Defeated [[Milan \u0160rejber]] (Czechoslovakia) 6-3 7-6 4-6 6-3\n:* Second round &mdash; Defeated [[Emilio S\u00e1nchez]] (Spain) 7-5 6-3 6-7 6-4\n:* Third round &mdash; Defeated [[Javier S\u00e1nchez (tennis)|Javier S\u00e1nchez]] (Spain) 7-6 4-6 6-1 6-2\n:* Quarterfinals &mdash; Lost to [[Stefan Edberg]] (Sweden) 1-6 5-7 4-6\n\n* [[Diego Nargiso]]\n:* First round &mdash; Defeated [[Francisco Maciel]] (Mexico) 4-6 2-6 7-6 7-6 8-6\n:* Second round &mdash; Lost to [[Tim Mayotte]] (United States) 6-2 2-6 4-6 0-6\n\n* [[Omar Camporese]]\n:* First round &mdash; Lost to [[Guy Forget]] (France) 2-6 0-6 3-6\n<br>\n'''Women's Singles Competition'''\n* [[Sandra Cecchini]]\n:* First Round &ndash; Bye \n:* Second Round &ndash; Lost to [[Chris Evert]] (USA) 2-6 2-6\n\n* [[Raffaella Reggi]]\n:* First Round &ndash; Defeated [[Liz Smylie]] (Australia) 7-6 6-0\n:* Second Round &ndash; Defeated [[Claudia Kohde-Kilsch]] (West Germany) 4-6 7-6 6-3 \n:* Third Round &ndash; Defeated [[Chris Evert]] (USA) 2-6 6-4 6-1 \n:* Quarterfinals &ndash; Lost to [[Manuela Maleeva]] (Switzerland) 3-6 4-6\n\n==Volleyball==\n{{main|Volleyball at the 1988 Summer Olympics}}\n\n===Men's Team Competition===\n*'''Preliminary Round (Group A)'''\n:* Lost to Brazil (0-3)\n:* Lost to Bulgaria (0-3)\n:* Defeated Sweden (3-2)\n:* Lost to Soviet Union (1-3)\n:* Defeated South Korea (3-0)\n*'''Classification Matches'''\n:* '''9th/12th place''': Defeated Tunisia (3-0)\n:* '''9th/10th place''': Defeated Japan (3-2) \u2192 '''Ninth place'''\n\n*'''Team Roster'''\n:*[[Andrea Gardini]]\n:*[[Andrea Giani]]\n:*[[Pierpaolo Lucchetta]]\n:*[[Ferdinando De Giorgi]]\n:*[[Marco Bracci]]\n:*[[Claudio Galli]]\n:*[[Lorenzo Bernardi]]\n:*[[Alessandro Lazzeroni]]\n:*[[Massimo Castagna]]\n:*[[Andrea Zorzi]]\n:*[[Luca Cantagalli]]\n:*[[Andrea Lucchetta]]\n*'''Head Coach''': [[Carmelo Pittera]]\n\n==Water polo==\n{{main|Water polo at the 1988 Summer Olympics}}\n'''Men's Team Competition'''\n* '''Preliminary Round (Group A)'''\n:* Drew with Soviet Union (9-9)\n:* Defeated South Korea (1-11)\n:* Defeated Australia (7-5)\n:* Lost to West Germany (7-10)\n:* Defeated France (14-8)\n* '''Classification Round (Group D)'''\n:* Drew with Hungary (9-9)\n:* Lost to Spain (9-11) \u2192 '''7th place'''\n\n* '''Team Roster'''\n:* [[Paolo Trapanese]]\n:* [[Alfio Misaggi]]\n:* [[Andrea Pisano (water polo)|Andrea Pisano]]\n:* [[Antonello Steardo]]\n:* [[Alessandro Campagna (water polo)|Alessandro Campagna]]\n:* [[Paolo Caldarella]]\n:* [[Mario Fiorillo]]\n:* [[Francesco Porzio]]\n:* [[Stefano Postiglione]]\n:* [[Riccardo Tempestini]]\n:* [[Massimiliano Ferretti]]\n:* [[Marco d'Altrui]]\n:* [[Gianni Averaimo]]\n*'''Head Coach''': [[Fritz Dennerlein]]\n\n==Weightlifting==\n{{main|Weightlifting at the 1988 Summer Olympics}}\n\n==Wrestling==\n{{main|Wrestling at the 1988 Summer Olympics}}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{commons category-inline}}\n\n{{country at games navbox|Italy|Olympics}}\n{{NOCin1988SummerOlympics}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Italy At The 1988 Summer Olympics}}\n[[Category:Nations at the 1988 Summer Olympics]]\n[[Category:Italy at the Summer Olympics by year|1988]]\n[[Category:1988 in Italian sport|Olympics]]\n", "text_old": "{{infobox country at games\n| NOC = ITA\n| NOCname = [[Italian National Olympic Committee]]\n| games = Summer Olympics\n| year = 1988\n| flagcaption = \n| oldcode = \n| website = {{url|www.coni.it }}&nbsp;{{in lang|it}}\n| location = [[Seoul]]\n| competitors = 253 (212 men, 41 women)\n| sports = 23\n| flagbearer = [[Pietro Mennea]]\n| rank = 10\n| gold = 6\n| silver = 4\n| bronze = 4\n| officials = \n| appearances = auto\n| app_begin_year = \n| app_end_year = \n| summerappearances = \n| winterappearances = \n| seealso = [[Italy at the 1906 Intercalated Games|1906]] Intercalated Games\n}}\n\n'''[[Italy]]''' competed at the '''[[1988 Summer Olympics]]''' in [[Seoul]], [[South Korea]]. 253 competitors, 212 men and 41 women, took part in 140 events in 23 sports.<ref name=\"sports-reference\">{{cite web|url=https://www.sports-reference.com/olympics/countries/ITA/summer/1988/ |title=Italy at the 1988 Summer Games |accessdate=2011-07-22 |work=sports-reference.com |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110630123952/http://www.sports-reference.com/olympics/countries/ITA/summer/1988/ |archivedate=2011-06-30 }}</ref>\n\n==Medalists==\n\n===Gold===\n* [[Gelindo Bordin]] \u2014 Athletics, Men's Marathon\n* [[Giovanni Parisi]] \u2014 Boxing, Men's Featherweight\n* [[Stefano Cerioni]] \u2014 Fencing, Men's Foil Individual Competition\n* [[Vincenzo Maenza]] \u2014 Wrestling, Men's Greco-Roman Light Flyweight \n* [[Carmine Abbagnale]], [[Giuseppe Abbagnale]] and [[Giuseppe Di Capua]] \u2014 Rowing, Men's Coxed Pairs  \n* [[Agostino Abbagnale]], [[Davide Tizzano]], [[Piero Poli]] and [[Gianluca Farina]] \u2014 Rowing, Men's Quadruple Sculls\n\n===Silver===\n* [[Carlo Massullo]] \u2014 Modern Pentathlon, Individual Competition\n* [[Carlo Massullo]], [[Daniele Masala]] and [[Gianluca Tiberti]] \u2014 Modern Pentathlon, Team Competition\n* [[Salvatore Antibo]] \u2014 Athletics, Men's 10.000 metres\n* [[Francesca Bortolozzi-Borella]], [[Dorina Vaccaroni]], [[Margherita Zalaffi]], [[Annapia Gandolfi]] and [[Lucia Traversa]] \u2014 Fencing, Women's  Foil Team Competition\n\n=== Bronze===\n* [[Maurizio Damilano]] \u2014 Athletics, Men's 20&nbsp;km Walk\n* [[Giovanni Scalzo]] \u2014 Fencing, Men's Sabre Individual Competition\n* [[Stefano Battistelli]] \u2014 Swimming, Men's 400 metres Individual Medley \n* [[Gianfranco Dalla Barba]], [[Marco Marin]], [[Ferdinando Meglio]], [[Giovanni Scalzo]] and [[Massimo Cavaliere]] \u2014 Fencing, Men's Sabre Team Competition\n\n==Archery==\n{{main|Archery at the 1988 Summer Olympics}}\n[[Giancarlo Ferrari]], competing in his fifth Olympic archery contest, dropped to 33rd place in the field.  Fellow veteran [[Ilario Di Bu\u00f2]] advanced to the quarterfinal, nearly missing a semifinal berth.  The Italians also just missed the cutoff for the final by one ranking in the team round.\n\n'''Men's Individual Competition:'''\n* [[Ilario Di Bu\u00f2]] &ndash; Quarterfinal (\u2192 13th place)\n* [[Andrea Parenti]] &ndash; Preliminary Round (\u2192 28th place)\n* [[Giancarlo Ferrari]] &ndash; Preliminary Round (\u2192 33rd place)\n\n'''Men's Team Competition:'''\n* Di Buo, Parenti, and Ferrari &ndash; Semifinal (\u2192 9th place)\n\n==Athletics==\n{{main|Athletics at the 1988 Summer Olympics}}\n'''Men's 10,000 metres''' \n* [[Salvatore Antibo]] \n:* First Round &mdash; 28:09.35\n:* Final &mdash; 27:23.55 (\u2192 [[File:Silver medal with cup.svg|16px|Silver]] '''Silver Medal''')\n\n* [[Alberto Cova]] \n:* First Round &mdash; 28:43.84 (\u2192 did not advance)\n\n'''Men's Marathon''' \n* [[Gelindo Bordin]] \n:* Final &mdash; 2\"10:32 (\u2192 [[Image:Gold medal with cup.svg|16px|Gold]] '''Gold Medal''')\n\n* [[Orlando Pizzolato]] \n:* Final &mdash; 2\"15:20 (\u2192 16th place)\n\n* [[Gianni Poli]] \n:* Final &mdash; 2\"16:07 (\u2192 19th place)\n\n'''Men's 3,000 m Steeplechase'''\n* [[Alessandro Lambruschini]]\n:# Heat &mdash; 8:32.59 \n:# Semi Final &mdash; 8:16.92\n:# Final &mdash; 8:12.17 (\u2192 4th place)\n\n* [[Francesco Panetta]]\n:* Heat &mdash; 8:29.75 \n:* Semi Final &mdash; 8:17.23\n:* Final &mdash; 8:17.79 (\u2192 9th place)\n\n'''Men's Hammer Throw'''\n* [[Lucio Serrani]]\n:* Qualifying Heat &mdash; 70.50m (\u2192 did not advance)\n\n'''Men's Shot Put'''\n* [[Alessandro Andrei]]\n:* Qualifying Heat &ndash; 20.18m\n:* Final &ndash; 20.36m (\u2192 7th place)\n\n'''Men's Long Jump''' \n* [[Giovanni Evangelisti]] \n:* Qualification &mdash; 7.81m\n:* Final &mdash; 8.08m (\u2192 4th place)\n\n'''Men's 20&n