Open|Stuttgart (Stockholm)]]\n|align=\"center\" style=\"background:#afeeee;\"|2R\n|align=\"center\" style=\"background:#afeeee;\"|3R\n|align=\"center\" style=\"background:#afeeee;\"|3R\n|align=\"center\" |A\n|align=\"center\" |A\n|align=\"center\" |A\n|align=\"center\" |A\n|align=\"center\" style=\"background:#EFEFEF;\"|0 / 3\n|- \n|style=\"background:#EFEFEF;\"|[[Paris Masters|Paris]]\n|align=\"center\" style=\"background:#afeeee;\"|1R\n|align=\"center\" style=\"background:#ffebcd;\"|QF\n|align=\"center\" style=\"background:#afeeee;\"|1R\n|align=\"center\" style=\"background:#afeeee;\"|3R\n|align=\"center\" |A\n|align=\"center\" |A\n|align=\"center\" |A\n|align=\"center\" style=\"background:#EFEFEF;\"|0 / 4\n|-bgcolor=\"#efefef\"\n|Masters Series SR\n|align=\"center\" colspan=\"6\" style=\"color:#ccc;\"|N/A\n|align=\"center\"|0 / 8\n|align=\"center\"|1 / 6\n|align=\"center\"|0 / 7\n|align=\"center\"|0 / 4\n|align=\"center\"|0 / 4\n|align=\"center\"|0 / 4\n|align=\"center\"|0 / 1\n|align=\"center\"|0 / 34\n|- \n|style=\"background:#EFEFEF;\"| Year End Ranking\n|align=\"center\"|138\n|align=\"center\"|159\n|align=\"center\"|33\n|align=\"center\"|76\n|align=\"center\"|127\n|align=\"center\"|74\n|align=\"center\"|34\n|align=\"center\" style=\"background:#EEE8AA;\"|8\n|align=\"center\"|23\n|align=\"center\"|17\n|align=\"center\"|28\n|align=\"center\"|121\n|align=\"center\"|409\n|align=\"center\" style=\"background:#EFEFEF;\"|N/A\n|}\n\n==See also==\n*[[List of sportspeople sanctioned for doping offences]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n* {{ATP}}\n* {{ITF}}\n* {{Davis Cup player}}\n\n{{ATP Masters Series tournament winners}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Novacek, Karel}}\n[[Category:1965 births]]\n[[Category:Czech male tennis players]]\n[[Category:Czechoslovak male tennis players]]\n[[Category:Doping cases in tennis]]\n[[Category:Hopman Cup competitors]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:People from Prost\u011bjov]]\n[[Category:Czech sportspeople in doping cases]]\n[[Category:Goodwill Games medalists in tennis]]\n", "text_old": "{{BLP sources|date=October 2015}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=July 2011}}\n{{Infobox tennis biography\n|name= Karel Nov\u00e1\u010dek\n|image= Karel Novacek-RG1994.jpg\n|country= {{TCH}} <small>(1984\u201392)</small><br />{{CZE}} <small>(1993\u201396)</small>\n|residence= [[Boca Raton, Florida]]\n|birth_date= {{birth date and age|1965|3|30|df=y}}\n|birth_place= [[Prost\u011bjov]], [[Czechoslovakia]]\n|height= {{height|m=1.90}}\n|turnedpro= 1984\n|retired= 1996\n|plays= Right-handed (one-handed backhand)\n|careerprizemoney= [[US$|$]]3,729,540\n|singlesrecord= 300\u2013246\n|singlestitles= 13\n|highestsinglesranking= No. 8 (18 November 1991)\n|AustralianOpenresult= 4R ([[1995 Australian Open \u2013 Men's Singles|1995]])\n|FrenchOpenresult= QF ([[1987 French Open \u2013 Men's Singles|1987]], [[1993 French Open \u2013 Men's Singles|1993]])\n|Wimbledonresult= 4R ([[1991 Wimbledon Championships \u2013 Men's Singles|1991]])\n|USOpenresult= SF ([[1994 U.S. Open - Men's Singles|1994]])\n|Othertournaments= Yes\n|MastersCupresult= RR ([[1991 ATP Tour World Championships - Singles|1991]])\n|doublesrecord= 168\u2013179\n|doublestitles= 6\n|highestdoublesranking= No. 25 (28 February 1994)\n}}\n\n'''Karel Nov\u00e1\u010dek''' (born 30 March 1965) is a retired [[Czech people|Czech]] former top ten [[tennis]] player born in [[Prost\u011bjov]], [[Czechoslovakia]] (Czech Republic). In his career, Nov\u00e1\u010dek won 13 singles titles and six doubles titles. His highest singles ranking was World No. 8, which he achieved on 18 November 1991.<ref>{{ITF profile|10001002}}</ref>\n\nHis best performance at a Grand Slam came at the [[1994 US Open (tennis)|1994 US Open]] where he defeated [[Alexander Vladimirovich Volkov]], [[Andriy Medvedev]], [[Todd Woodbridge]], [[Javier Frana]] and [[Jaime Yzaga]] before losing to [[Michael Stich]] in the semifinal. In 1997, Novacek was suspended for three months for failing a drug test at the 1995 French Open; he forfeited $185,765, but denied taking [[cocaine]] knowingly.<ref>{{cite news | url=https://www.nytimes.com/1997/05/15/sports/wilander-and-novacek-are-banned.html | title= Wilander and Novacek are banned | date=15 May 1997| newspaper=[[New York Times]] |accessdate=29 October 2015}}</ref>\n\nNov\u00e1\u010dek lived in [[Boca Raton, Florida]], United States for 20 years, and then moved back to Czech Republic. Karel and Maya Nov\u00e1\u010dek married in 1990; as of 2002, they had three children.<ref name=BRN>{{cite news |title=There's a new Novacek in town |author=Tom Glucksmann |newspaper=Boca Raton News |date=25 December 2002 |url=https://news.google.com/newspapers?nid=1291&dat=20021225&id=vFpUAAAAIBAJ&sjid=ko4DAAAAIBAJ&pg=5549,7347121&hl=en}}</ref> In 2002, the ''[[Boca Raton News]]'' reported that their ten-year-old daughter Anika was a promising tennis player, winning several tournaments.<ref name=BRN/>\n\n== Career finals ==\n\n=== Singles (13 titles, 7 runners-up) ===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable mw-collapsible mw-collapsed\" \n|- style=\"background:#eeeeee;\"\n|'''Legend (Singles)'''\n|- style=\"background:#f3e6d7;\"\n| Grand Slam (0\u20130)\n|- style=\"background:#ffffcc;\"\n| Tennis Masters Cup (0\u20130)\n|- style=\"background:#e9e9e9;\"\n| ATP Masters Series (1\u20130)\n|-\n| ATP Tour (12\u20137)\n|}\n{|class=\"sortable wikitable\" \n!style=\"width:40px\"|Result\n!style=\"width:30px\"|'''No.'''\n!style=\"width:50px\"|'''Year'''\n!style=\"width:180px\"|'''Tournament'''\n!style=\"width:60px\"|'''Surface'''\n!style=\"width:200px\"|'''Opponent'''\n!style=\"width:170px\" class=\"unsortable\"|'''Score'''\n|-\n|style=\"background:#ffa07a;\"|Loss\n|1.\n|1986\n|[[Erste Bank Open|Vienna]], Austria\n|Hard (i)\n|{{flagicon|USA}} [[Gary Donnelly]]\n|2\u20136, 6\u20137\n|-\n|style=\"background:#98fb98;\"|Win\n|1.\n|1986\n|[[Legg Mason Tennis Classic|Washington]], U.S.\n|Clay\n|{{flagicon|FRA}} [[Thierry Tulasne]]